Has Hollywood ever rooted harder for one billionaire=E2=80=99s kid to buy a=
 company from another billionaire=E2=80=99s kid? With apologies to HBO=E2=
=80=99s Girls, David Ellison=E2=80=99s on, off, then on-again deal to merge=
 his Skydance Media with Shari Redstone=E2=80=99s Paramount Global is almos=
t certainly Peak Nepo Baby, right?

Still, I think there was a bit of an exhale around town last night as the p=
ress releases hit. Barring some unlikely regulatory hiccup or an alternativ=
e suitor=E2=80=94like Barry Diller or Edgar Bronfman Jr. or Apollo Global t=
aking advantage of the 45 day =E2=80=9Cgo-shop=E2=80=9D provision to make t=
he Paramount special board committee a better offer=E2=80=94the home of the=
 Paramount studio, CBS, the cable channels, and streamers is being sold to =
someone who actually wants to be in this business for a while. Like I=E2=80=
=99ve
been saying for months now, this is probably the best-case scenario for the=
se assets=E2=80=94and for Hollywood, a business in secular decline that jus=
t got a major boost from the billionaire class.

Think about it: The Ellison family and RedBird Capital are investing more t=
han $8 billion in a company that the public market is valuing at only about=
 that much as a whole, minus debt. That=E2=80=99s $6 billion from Larry=E2=
=80=99s $160 billion Oracle fortune and $2 billion from RedBird=E2=80=94$1.=
5 billion to pay down that $14 billion or so in debt, $4.5 billion in Param=
ount shares, and about $1.75 billion for National Amusements, the Redstone =
holding company, which is valued in this deal at $2.4 billion (including de=
bt). No offense to the other suitors of varying seriousness (even Byron All=
en!), but who other than the Ellisons are willing to put that kind of perso=
nal money into a company that makes most of its revenue from linear televis=
ion?

This isn=E2=80=99t quite a
Jeff Bezos buying the Washington Post charity mission, but the Ellisons wer=
e certainly motivated buyers. David wanted this; Shari wanted someone who w=
ould keep her dad=E2=80=99s legacy relatively intact; David=E2=80=99s fathe=
r, as the 10th-richest person in the world and pushing 80 years old, is in =
the position to buy this company for his son; so=E2=80=A6 deal done. For a =
transaction so financially complex, it=E2=80=99s not that complicated.

That=E2=80=99s the reason I never thought the Skydance-Paramount deal was t=
otally dead, even when both Skydance and Paramount told us all last month t=
hat it was totally dead. It=E2=80=99s the same reason I took the Ellison ov=
erture seriously when I first revealed it ( https://puck.news/shari-inches-=
toward-parting-with-paramount/?utm_campaign=3DWhat+I%27m+Hearing+-+SUBSCRIB=
