          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">Has Hollywood ever =
rooted harder for one billionaire=E2=80=99s kid to buy a company from anoth=
er billionaire=E2=80=99s kid? With apologies to HBO=E2=80=99s <i>Girls</i>,=
 <b>David Ellison</b>=E2=80=99s on, off, then on-again deal to merge his Sk=
ydance Media with <b>Shari Redstone</b>=E2=80=99s Paramount Global is almos=
t certainly Peak Nepo Baby, right?  <br/> <br/>Still, I think there was a b=
it of an exhale around town last night as the press releases hit. Barring s=
ome unlikely regulatory hiccup or an alternative suitor=E2=80=94like <b>Bar=
ry Diller</b> or <b>Edgar Bronfman Jr.</b> or Apollo Global taking advantag=
e of the 45 day =E2=80=9Cgo-shop=E2=80=9D provision to make the Paramount s=
pecial board committee a better offer=E2=80=94the home of the Paramount stu=
dio, CBS, the cable channels, and streamers is being sold to someone who <i=
>actually wants to be in this business for a while</i>. Like I=E2=80=99ve
been saying for months now, this is probably the best-case scenario for the=
se assets=E2=80=94and for Hollywood, a business in secular decline that jus=
t got a major boost from the billionaire class.<br/> <br/>Think about it: T=
he Ellison family and RedBird Capital are investing more than $8 billion in=
 a company that the public market is valuing at only about that much <i>as =
a whole</i>, minus debt. That=E2=80=99s $6 billion from <b>Larry</b>=E2=80=
=99s $160 billion Oracle fortune and $2 billion from RedBird=E2=80=94$1.5 b=
illion to pay down that $14 billion or so in debt, $4.5 billion in Paramoun=
t shares, and about $1.75 billion for National Amusements, the Redstone hol=
ding company, which is valued in this deal at $2.4 billion (including debt)=
=2E No offense to the other suitors of=20=
varying seriousness (even <b>Byron All=
en</b>!), but who other than the Ellisons are willing to put that kind of p=
ersonal money into a company that makes most of its revenue from linear tel=
evision? <br/><br/>This isn=E2=80=99t quite a
<b>Jeff Bezos</b> buying the <i>Washington Post</i> charity mission, but th=
e Ellisons were certainly <i>motivated</i> buyers. David wanted this; Shari=
 wanted someone who would keep her dad=E2=80=99s legacy relatively intact; =
David=E2=80=99s father, as the 10th-richest person in the world and pushing=
 80 years old, is in the position to buy this company for his son; so=E2=80=
=A6 deal done. For a transaction so financially complex, it=E2=80=99s not t=
hat complicated. <br/> <br/>That=E2=80=99s the reason I never thought the S=
kydance-Paramount deal was totally dead, even when both Skydance and Paramo=
unt told us all last month that it was totally dead. It=E2=80=99s the same =
reason I took the Ellison overture seriously when I <u><a href=3D"https://e=
