hanges will start before the Skydance merger is official. That means some v=
ersion of the cost-cutting and asset-shedding plan articulated by Shari=E2=
=80=99s three placeholder C.E.O.s=E2=80=94including, I=E2=80=99m surmising,=
 the massive layoffs, the planned sale of BET Media, I.P. deals (I=E2=80=99=
m told Paramount is already talking to <b>Jamie Salter </b>and his Authenti=
c Brands Group about exploiting its lesser kids characters), and a streamin=
g joint venture with Amazon, NBCUniversal, or another player. =E2=80=9CNo, =
it has not stopped,=E2=80=9D Ellison told me of the Redstone-endorsed strat=
egic plan, =E2=80=9Cwithin all the regulatory bounds.=E2=80=9D Skydance wil=
l have =E2=80=9Cthe appropriate seat at the tables,=E2=80=9D he continued, =
=E2=80=9Cand
we have confidence in that team.=E2=80=9D<br/> <br/>So, basically, Ellison =
and his president, former NBCU C.E.O. <b>Jeff Shell</b>, will be as involve=
d as allowed legally over the next year or so. And <b>George Cheeks</b>, <b=
>Chris McCarthy</b>, and <b>Brian Robbins</b> will go about cutting costs, =
selling assets, and doing joint ventures with the tacit approval of the new=
 owners? =E2=80=9CCorrect,=E2=80=9D Ellison told me.  <br/> <br/>2. <i>Big =
cuts in linear</i>: Shell will almost certainly gut the linear TV assets ev=
en further. =E2=80=9CThey are very profitable businesses that do need to be=
 managed differently,=E2=80=9D Ellison told me. =E2=80=9CThey need to be ma=
naged for cash flow.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s been happening for a while now=
, of course=E2=80=94the unscripted/game show boom in broadcast, the McCarth=
y <i>Ridiculousness</i> strategy of airing endless repeats on each cable ne=
twork to supplement a signature franchise that kinda maybe justifies the ch=
annel=E2=80=99s existence. The risk, obviously, is that further content
