end domestic debut ($75 million Fri-Sun and $122 million Wed-Sun) is how mu=
ch the movie lured younger demographics: A whopping <i>74 percent </i>of th=
e audience was under age 35. Yes, obviously, this is a <i>kids=E2=80=99 </i=
>movie, but the heightened percentage suggests that young adults were also =
reconnecting with Gru, the minions, the <b>Pharrell </b>soundtrack, and cha=
racters of their own youths. This continues a pattern for most of the year=
=E2=80=99s big box office successes: Out of generational nostalgia, young a=
udiences are flocking to franchises that were birthed during the 2010s. <br=
/><br/>During the past year, the most successful films have included new in=
stallments of <i>Kung Fu Panda </i>and <i>The Hunger Games</i>. <i>Inside O=
ut 2</i> has been an outsized hit
($1.21 billion and counting) partially because of nostalgia for the origina=
l, from 2015, which became a generational Pixar touchstone=E2=80=94just lik=
e <i>Finding Nemo </i>and <i>Toy Story </i>before it. Likewise, <i>Despicab=
le Me </i>was an entirely new animated comedy in the summer of 2010, pitche=
d at young kids even as it told a tale of midlife crisis. <i>Minions</i>, i=
ts summer 2015 spinoff, grossed $1.1 billion amid an all-quadrant franchise=
 revival, and now <i>Despicable Me 4 </i>is marching toward at least $700 m=
illion worldwide, and probably much more, on a $100 million budget.<br/><br=
/><i>Deadpool &amp; Wolverine</i>, coming out later this month, seems poise=
d to draft on the same nostalgia kick. In 2016, <i>Deadpool </i>became a bl=
ockbuster mostly because audiences who otherwise couldn=E2=80=99t have pick=
ed Deadpool, Deadshot, and Deathstroke out of a lineup found the notion of =
<b>Ryan Reynolds </b>playing a fourth-wall-breaking antihero in an R-rated =
rom-com superhero parody
largely irresistible. If the kids who grew up on <i>Inside Out </i>and <i>D=
espicable Me </i>were too young to see <i>Deadpool </i>and <i>Deadpool 2 </=
i>in theaters, they=E2=80=99re old enough now to see the third film. <br/><=
br/>The other definitive trend this year has been reincarnations of older f=
ranchises, like <i>Bad Boys: Ride or Die</i>, that intentionally played as =
